  "prompt": "What was the public's reaction to Crystal Pepsi?",
  "response": "Crystal Pepsi, a clear soda introduced by PepsiCo in the early 1990s, received a mixed reaction from the public. When it was launched in 1992, it was marketed as a caffeine-free, transparent alternative to colas, emphasizing its purity and health aspects. The novelty of the product initially attracted attention and consumer curiosity, leading to strong initial sales.\n\nHowever, over time, consumer taste preferences and expectations shifted. Many people were confused by the idea of a clear cola, and the flavor did not resonate with everyone. Some consumers felt it tasted different from traditional colas, leading to disappointment. Sales began to decline, and Crystal Pepsi was eventually discontinued in 1994.\n\nIn retrospective analysis, Crystal Pepsi has become somewhat of a pop culture icon, often discussed in the context of failed products. Its legacy includes nostalgia for those who enjoyed it and curiosity about its unique concept, leading to periodic limited-time re-releases and marketing campaigns that capitalize on its cult status. Overall, Crystal Pepsi's introduction sparked intrigue, but its long-term reception was more negative, ultimately cementing it as a fascinating moment in beverage marketing history.",
